Thepoorer classes at Rome lived in tenement houses called insulae, about the construction of which we have scanty informa— tion. They were carried up to a great height (vs. 269 n), were often cheaply built, and rendered still more insecure by the neglect of necessary repairs. The falling oi such buildings was a constant source of danger.
